column2: Stricter environmental laws and regulations are worth the cost.
column3: I feel distressed when I see news related to environmental disasters.
column4: I believe that environmental issues will negatively impact my future quality of life.
column5: I worry that the planet will not be livable for future generations.
column6: Companies should be held accountable for their environmental impact, even if it increases the prices of goods.
column7: I sometimes avoid learning about environmental issues because it feels too distressing.
column8: I feel hopeless about the possibility of reversing the effects of climate change.
column9: I feel overwhelmed by the amount of information about climate change and environmental problems.
column10: I believe governments should prioritize climate change over economic growth.
column11: I feel guilty if I engage in activities that harm the environment, even minimally.
